    <div class="header">
        <h1>SIP Portal</h1>
        <p>Your gateway to smart investments</p>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="content">
            <h1>What is a Systematic Investment Plan (SIP)?</h1>
            <p>A Systematic Investment Plan (SIP) is a method of investing a fixed sum regularly in a mutual fund scheme. It allows investors to buy units of the scheme on a particular date each month, thus building a disciplined investment habit. SIPs are designed to help investors accumulate wealth over the long term by investing small amounts of money at regular intervals.</p>
            
            <h2>Benefits of SIP</h2>
            <p>SIPs offer several benefits to investors:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Disciplined Saving:</strong> SIPs instill a sense of financial discipline by encouraging regular saving and investment.</li>
                <li><strong>Rupee Cost Averaging:</strong> SIPs average out the purchase cost of mutual fund units over time, reducing the impact of market volatility.</li>
                <li><strong>Power of Compounding:</strong> By investing regularly and over a long period, investors can benefit from the power of compounding, where returns generate further returns.</li>
                <li><strong>Flexibility:</strong> SIPs are flexible; investors can start, stop, or modify their SIPs as per their financial goals and needs.</li>
                <li><strong>Convenience:</strong> SIPs are easy to set up and automate, making the investment process hassle-free.</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h2>How to Start a SIP</h2>
            <p>Starting a SIP is simple and can be done in a few steps:</p>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Select a Mutual Fund Scheme:</strong> Choose a mutual fund scheme that aligns with your investment goals and risk appetite.</li>
                <li><strong>Complete KYC:</strong> Ensure that you have completed the Know Your Customer (KYC) process.</li>
                <li><strong>Register for SIP:</strong> Fill out the SIP registration form with details like the amount, frequency, and tenure of the investment.</li>
                <li><strong>Set Up Auto-Debit:</strong> Link your bank account for auto-debit to ensure timely investments.</li>
                <li><strong>Track and Review:</strong> Monitor your SIP investments regularly and make adjustments if needed to stay aligned with your financial goals.</li>
            </ol>
            
            <h2>Contact Us</h2>
            <p>If you have any questions or need assistance, please contact our support team at <a href="mailto:support@sipportal.com">support@sipportal.com</a>.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="footer">
        <p>&copy; 2024 SIP Portal. All rights reserved.</p>
    </div>
</body>
